Boil a large #pot{} of water for the @quinoa{170%grams}.

When boiling, add the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} powder and stir to dissolve.

Stir in the quinoa and bring back to the boil.

Cook until the quinoa has doubled in size and the seed has visibly split, ~{12-15%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Cover with a #lid{} and set aside.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, cut the @tomato{2}(cut into 1cm cubes) into 1cm cubes.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%pack} in a sieve.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the beans with the @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} until fragrant, ~{4-5%mins}.

In a large #bowl{}, make your dressing by mixing the @harissa spice mix{1%sachet}, the juice of @lime{1}(juiced), @oil{2%tsp}(for dressing), @salt{½%tsp}(for dressing) and @sugar{1%tsp}(for dressing).

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the pit.

Cut the avocado into chunks (while still in its skin) then use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh into the bowl with the dressing.

Add the @salad leaves{40%grams}, quinoa, beans and tomato to the bowl.

Crumble in half the @Greek style cheese{100%grams}.

Mix well and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the warm quinoa salad between #bowls{}.

Top with a crumbling of the remaining cheese.